{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2011}} {{Infobox racecourse |name = Canterbury Park Racecourse |image = CanterburyRacecourse.jpg |caption =Canterbury Park Racecourse |location = [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]] |coordinates = {{Coord|-33.906824|151.115398|format=dms|type:landmark_region:AU-NSW|display=title,inline}} |owner = [[Australian Turf Club]] |operator = |opened = 1871 |closed = |channel = |racetype = |coursetype = |notableraces = |handle = |attendance = |website = http://www.australianturfclub.com.au/ }}
'''Canterbury Park Racecourse''' is a [[racecourse]] for [[horse racing]] in [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]]. It is located 11&nbsp;km (7&nbsp;mi) from the [[Sydney Central Business District]], in King Street in the suburb of [[Canterbury, New South Wales|Canterbury]], adjacent to [[Canterbury railway station, Sydney|Canterbury railway station]]. The racecourse is operated by the [[Australian Turf Club]].
== History == The first horse racing in [[Canterbury, New South Wales|Canterbury]] was in 1852 when Cornelius Proud cleared part of his property for use as a racecourse, this was used regularly by locals. In 1871, after a few years with no race meetings being held, Frederick Clissold and Thomas Austen Davis held a race meeting on land that had been [[lease]]d by Davis close to the existing racecourse.<ref name="LawrenceMuir1999">{{cite book|author1=Joan Lawrence|author2=Lawrence, Madden & Muir|author3=Brian J. Madden|author4=Lesley Muir|title=Pictorial History Canterbury Bankstown|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=H1Aiy3Pla-EC&pg=PA46|accessdate=26 March 2013|year=1999|publisher=Kingsclear Books Pty Ltd|isbn=978-0-908272-55-6|page=46}}</ref> In 1884 the site was leased as the headquarters of Canterbury Park Race Club.<ref name="environment.nsw.gov.au">[http://www.environment.nsw.gov.au/heritageapp/ViewHeritageItemDetails.aspx?ID=1300002 NSW Government: Canterbury park Racecourse]</ref> A racetrack, 700 person grandstand and recreational park was constructed and held its first meeting on the 19th January 1884.<ref>[http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/10155275?versionId=176840074 National Library of Australia Archive]</ref> In 1886, 53 acres of the leased land was purchased by Davis for use by the club.
Up until [[World War I]] there was a zoo located on site that housed animals such as [[Kangaroo]]s, [[Wallaby|Wallabies]], [[Emu]]s, [[Brolga]]s, [[Curlew]]s, [[Pheasant]]s and [[Kookaburra]]s.<ref name="LawrenceMuir1999"/>
The Sydney Turf Club (STC) acquired the racecourse and held its first meeting in January 1945.<ref name="environment.nsw.gov.au"/> The STC held the racecourse until 2011 when the Sydney Turf Club and Australian Jockey Club merged to become the [[Australian Turf Club]]. The [[Australian Turf Club]] are the current owners and operators of Canterbury Park Racecourse.<ref>[https://www.australianturfclub.com.au/canterbury-park/ Australian Turf Club - Canterbury Park]</ref>
