{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}
{{Use British English|date=February 2016}}
'''John Dampier''' (1750 – 18 August 1826) was an English amateur [[cricket]]er in the late 18th century. His place of birth is unknown but he was educated at [[Eton College]]. He died in [[Ely, Cambridgeshire]] when he was either 75 or 76 years old.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/80/80067/80067.html John Dampier on CricketArchive]</ref> He made five known appearances for the [[White Conduit Club]] team, based at [[White Conduit Fields]] in [[Islington]], between 1785 and 1787. He was an early member of [[Marylebone Cricket Club]] (MCC) which was founded in 1787, but he is not known to have played for MCC.<ref name=S&B>[[Arthur Haygarth]], ''Scores & Biographies'', Volume 1 (1744–1826), Lillywhite, 1862, pp. 62–71.</ref>

