{{Update|date=March 2018}} {{infobox hockey team | team = Viru Sputnik | colour = blue | colour text = yellow | logo = | logosize = 150px | city = [[Kohtla-Järve]], [[Estonia]] | league = [[Meistriliiga (ice hockey)|Meistriliiga]] | conference = | division = | founded = {{Start date|2003}} | operated = | arena = [[Kohtla-Järve Jäähall]] | colours = {{Color box|blue|border=darkgray}} {{Color box|yellow|border=darkgray}} {{Color box|white|border=darkgray}} | owner = | GM = Sergei Konõšev | coach = G. Eremeyev | captain = | affiliates = | parentclub = | farmclub = | website = {{URL|http://www.virusputnik.ee}} }}
'''Viru Sputnik''' is an [[Estonia]]n [[ice hockey]] team playing in the [[Meistriliiga (ice hockey)|Meistriliiga]]. The club is based in [[Kohtla-Järve]] and the home arena is [[Kohtla-Järve Jäähall]]. Viru Sputnik has played in Meistriliiga since it was established in 2003.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:История "Виру Спутник"|url=http://www.virusputnik.ee/viewpage.php?page_id=13|publisher=Viru Sputnik|accessdate=1 June 2011|language=Russian}}</ref>
In [[2009–10 Meistriliiga season|2009–10 season]] they became the Estonian champions, [[2008–09 Meistriliiga season|2008–09]] and [[2010–11 Meistriliiga season|2010–11 season]] they placed second.<ref name=medalikolmikud>{{cite web|title=Medalikolmikud|url=http://www.icehockey.ee/en/eesti-mv/statistika.html|publisher=Estonian Ice Hockey Association|accessdate=1 June 2011|language=Estonian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110829160700/http://www.icehockey.ee/en/eesti-mv/statistika.html|archivedate=29 August 2011|df=}}</ref>
