{{BLP sources|date=October 2009}} [http://media.gettyimages.com/photos/omar-nejjary-raja-casablanca-picture-id650837710?s=594x594]{{Infobox football biography | image = | name= Omar Nejjary | fullname = Omar Nejjary | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1972|6|27}} | birth_place = [[Casablanca]], [[Morocco]] | height = | currentclub = Raja Casablanca | clubnumber = | position = Midfielder | youthyears1 = ?–1990 | youthclubs1 = [[Raja Casablanca]] | years1 = 1990–2010 | clubs1 = [[Raja Casablanca]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | nationalyears1 = 1996 | nationalteam1 = [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | pcupdate = April 16, 2009 | ntupdate = October 17, 2008 }} '''Omar Nejjary''' is a retired [[Morocco|Moroccan]] [[football (soccer)|footballer]]. He usually played as [[midfielder (association football)|midfielder]].
Nejjary spent his entire career at [[Raja Casablanca]] and played for his club at the [[2000 FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref>{{FIFA player|176579}}</ref>
