hive.org/web/20180725183928/https://www.sport24.co.za/OtherSport/BetCentre/winner-of-2017-office-superbru-pool-reckons-he-knows-a-thing-or-two-20180219 | archive-date = July 25, 2018 | dead-url = no | df = mdy-all }}</ref><ref name="busi_Thes">{{Cite web | title = These SA data scientists have had great success with predicting World Cup scores - and they believe they know who will win the tournament | author = | work = businessinsider.co.za | date = | accessdate = July 25, 2018 | url = https://www.businessinsider.co.za/these-sa-data-scientists-say-france-will-win-the-2018-fifa-world-cup-2-0-against-croatia-based-on-this-method-2018-7 | language = | quote = | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180725183705/https://www.businessinsider.co.za/these-sa-data-scientists-say-france-will-win-the-2018-fifa-world-cup-2-0-against-croatia-based-on-this-method-2018-7 | archive-date = July 25, 2018 | dead-url = no | df = mdy-all }}</ref> [[English Premier League]],<ref name="brea_Week">{{Cite web | title = Weekend Premier League Predictions With Superbru | author = | work = Breathe Chelsea | date = | accessdate = July 25, 2018 | url = https://www.breathechelsea.com/weekend-premier-league-predictions-with-superbru-2/ | quote = | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180726112934/https://www.breathechelsea.com/weekend-premier-league-predictions-with-superbru-2/ | archive-date = July 26, 2018 | dead-url = no | df = mdy-all }}</ref> or [[The Championships, Wimbledon|Wimbledon]], across different sports, such as [[Rugby League]] and [[Cycling]].
Superbru has been used to show how data scientists can correctly predict scores; such as ''Principa'' correctly predicting 99.5% of scores from the [[2015 Rugby World Cup]].<ref name="thes_Adat">{{Cite web | title = A data company predicted Japan's win over Boks and is beating the Rugby World Cup bookies | last = Muller | first = Antoinette | work = The South African | date = July 25, 2018 | accessdate = July 25, 2018 | url = https://www.thesouthafrican.com/a-data-company-predicted-japans-win-over-boks-and-is-beating-the-rugby-world-cup-bookies/ | quote = | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160208083055/http://www.thesouthafrican.com/a-data-company-predicted-japans-win-over-boks-and-is-beating-the-rugby-world-cup-bookies/ | archive-date = February 8, 2016 | dead-url = no | df = mdy-all }}</ref><ref name="itwe_Anal">{{Cite web | title = Analytics, machine learning predict World Cup scores | author = ITWeb | last2 = Moyo | first2 = Admire | work = ITWeb | date = | accessdate = July 25, 2018 | url = https://www.itweb.co.za/content/LPp6VMr4AYbvDKQz | quote = | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180725184038/https://www.itweb.co.za/content/LPp6VMr4AYbvDKQz | archive-date = July 25, 2018 | dead-url = no | df = mdy-all }}</ref> As of 2018, Superbru has over 1.5 million registered users.<ref name="about"/><ref name="mone_Awin">{{Cite web | title = A winning strategy for investing and Superbru | author = | work = Moneyweb | date = | accessdate = July 25, 2018 | url = https://www.moneyweb.co.za/uncategorized/a-winning-strategy-for-investing-and-superbru-2/ | language = | quote = | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306061122/http://www.moneyweb.co.za/uncategorized/a-winning-strategy-for-investing-and-superbru-2/ | archive-date = March 6, 2016 | dead-url = no | df = mdy-all }}</ref>
==History== SuperBru was founded in 2001 as a Super 12's prediction game, in the [[University of Cape Town]], as a paper based league. In 2003, the game was merged online, with access not available to the public. In 2006, Superbru was opened; with financial support from web design company ''[[Nevado]]'', and later created a [[United Kingdom]] version, called ''Sports Guru''.{{efn|SportsGuru would later merge into Superbru in 2012.<ref name="about">{{Cite web | title = Superbru - About Us | author = | work = superbru.com | date = | accessdate = July 25, 2018 | url = https://www.superbru.com/home/about.php | language = | quote = | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170517111515/http://www.superbru.com/home/about.php | archive-date = May 17, 2017 | dead-url = no | df = mdy-all }}</ref>}} In 2011, Superbru moved away from Nevado, creating ''SportsEngage'', financing the website.<ref name="about"/>
