{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Robert Mensah Sports Stadium | nickname = Tema Park | image = | location = [[Tema]], [[Ghana]] | opened = 2008 | owner = | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | capacity = 5,000 | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[Tema Youth]] and [[Real Sportive]] | seating_capacity = 5,000 }} '''Robert Mensah Sports Stadium''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Tema]], [[Ghana]]. It used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Tema Youth]] and [[Real Sportive]]. The stadium holds 5,000 people. It was an artificial pitch the African Cup of Nations 2008, by the tournament called as Tema Sports Stadium.
